"{\"uid\": \"newsweek.com-olympics-athletes-bedbugs-south-korea-1938548\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Published  Aug 13, 2024 at 10:01 AM EDT  updated  Aug 13, 2024 at 11:32 AM EDT  News Reporter  South Korea has placed a bedbug sniffer dog at its main international airport to try to prevent the insects entering the country from the ParisOlympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 95, \"end\": 106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9998201954111354, \"rank\": 0.00017983692198507295, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ceco, a two-year-old beagle, is leading the bedbug detection efforts at the Incheon International Airport in Seoul.\", \"from\": 249, \"to\": 364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 325, \"end\": 354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Incheon_International_Airport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Incheon International Airport\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Incheon_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Incheon_International_Airport\"}, {\"begin\": 358, \"end\": 363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Incheon_International_Airport\", \"score\": 0.792887666812136, \"rank\": 0.2578122593351744, \"text\": \"Seoul\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Incheon_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Incheon_International_Airport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pest control company Cesco trained the dog to sniff out pheromones, the chemicals released by bedbugs, according to the Korea Post.\", \"from\": 366, \"to\": 497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 486, \"end\": 496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korea_Post\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Korea Post\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korea_Post\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korea_Post\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The company said that Ceco has an accuracy of at least 95 percent in detecting bedbugs.\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 586, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Ceco can detect bedbugs far more faster than the human eye, identifying every stage of bedbug life, from eggs to adults, within just 1 to 2 minutes per room-a significant advantage for the hospitality industry,\\\" the company said, per the Korea Post.\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 827, \"end\": 837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korea_Post\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Korea Post\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korea_Post\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korea_Post\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Korea Disease Control and Prevention Agency said the dog had been deployed at an airport booth, along with a human bedbug control expert, which will remain active until September 8.\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 1025, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 844, \"end\": 849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999158869125011, \"rank\": 7.219429352952193e-05, \"text\": \"Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Passengers coming from areas at risk of bedbug infestations can be checked at the booth and receive extermination services if needed.\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1160, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If bedbugs are found, they can be exterminated using a steam gun, ultraprecision microscope, and a special hot air chamber, as the bugs die at temperatures above 113 degrees Fahrenheit.\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1336, \"end\": 1346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fahrenheit\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0522897636446586e-28, \"text\": \"Fahrenheit\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fahrenheit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fahrenheit\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The airport is also enhancing quarantine and disinfection measures, including by regularly disinfecting aircraft, with a focus on those coming from Paris.\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1503, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1497, \"end\": 1502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999991155164, \"rank\": 8.8449376262917e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hub will also regularly be disinfected in areas with high passenger traffic.\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1585, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lee Han-kyung, the head of the Disaster and Safety Management Headquarters of the Ministry of the Interior and Safety, said: \\\"It is important to block the inflow of bedbugs in advance because it is difficult to control them once they are discovered.\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1587, \"end\": 1590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"score\": 0.9992147495772956, \"rank\": 0.0006746053767453115, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Therefore, we will strengthen preemptive blocking measures starting from the airport through public-private cooperation.\\\"\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1958, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"South Korea sent 144 athletes to compete at the Olympics in Paris.\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 2026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1960, \"end\": 1971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9998201954111354, \"rank\": 0.00017983692198507295, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 2020, \"end\": 2025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999991155164, \"rank\": 8.8449376262917e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Along with the athletes, other officials, trainers, and spectators also traveled to the French capital.\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2130, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2115, \"end\": 2121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8114291032048025, \"rank\": 0.15553117387532417, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris had a bedbugoutbreak in late 2023which sparked widespread media attention.\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2132, \"end\": 2137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999991155164, \"rank\": 8.8449376262917e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was reported that the insects were infestingthe Paris metro systemand buses, along with various other public places.\", \"from\": 2214, \"to\": 2333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2265, \"end\": 2270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999991155164, \"rank\": 8.8449376262917e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Videos went viral showing the creatures spotted in various locations around the city.\", \"from\": 2334, \"to\": 2419, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The infestation, less than a year before the 2024 Paris Olympics, had sparked some concerns about the city's ability to safely host the event.\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2563, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, so far, there have been no signs that the Olympics have causedthe spread of bedbugs.\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2658, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Late last year South Korea also had its own bedbug outbreak, which sparked a firm nationwide crackdown.\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2675, \"end\": 2686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9998201954111354, \"rank\": 0.00017983692198507295, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The small, parasitic insects feed on the blood of humans and animals, typically causing itchy bites and discomfort.\", \"from\": 2765, \"to\": 2880, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They often are found in mattresses, furniture, and other soft fabrics.\", \"from\": 2881, \"to\": 2951, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a92025Newsweek Digital LLC\", \"from\": 2953, \"to\": 2978, \"entities\": []}]}"